<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Former Home Secretary Jacqui Smith has shown off her Strictly Come Dancing transformation in a plunging sequin gown as she 'teased things to come'.</p>

<p>Taking to Twitter, the 57-year-old looked incredible as she posed in a plunging sequin dress, with heavy make-up and curled hair. </p>

<p>She wrote: 'The <?php echo e('@'); ?>bbcstrictly wardrobe, hair and makeup teams are genius.' </p>

<p>'The glam teams are genius': Former Home Secretary Jacqui Smith, 57, revealed her Strictly transformation on Twitter, wearing in plunging sequin gown as she 'teased things to come'</p>

<p>Jacqui added: 'Here’s a little tease of things to come! (Of course I look like this every weekend when recording <?php echo e('@'); ?>forthemanypod and that <?php echo e('@'); ?>IainDale [her co-star on the For The Many podcast] is a fiend for the sequins).</p>

<p>Fellow Strictly contestant, Good Morning Britain presenter Ranvir Singh posted a fire emoji and wrote that Jacqui looked 'sensational'.  </p>

<p>Jacqui said when she was announced as one of the final contestants on the show 'I was speechless with excitement at being asked to join Strictly – and that's very rare for me...</p>

<p>Changing things up: She had ditched her customary boxy jackets (left in 2009) in favour of a sleek new look (right) when she appeared on the Andrew Marr show back in 2017 </p>

<p>'Fifty years ago, I got a bronze medal for Scottish Highland Dancing and it feels about time to return to dancing. </p>

<p>'I couldn't be in better hands with the Strictly team and I'm going to throw myself into the challenge. Watch out!'.   </p>

<p>She will join HRVY, Jason Bell, Ranvir Singh, Clara Amfo, Caroline Quentin, Jamie Laing, Bill Bailey, JJ Chalmers, Max George, Maisie Smith and Nicola Adams. </p>

<p>Jacqui was one of the original 'Blair Babes' of 1997, and shocked with a glam transformation when she appeared on the Andrew Marr show in 2017.  </p>

<p>Fans of the show took to Twitter to declare she was unrecognisable, having a new workout regime and ditching her favoured boxy jackets in favour of a simple navy shift dress. </p>

<p>Her striped blonde highlights and fringe had also been replaced with a sleek brunette.  </p>

<p>Her time in office was marked by a series of blunders, including saying she would not feel safe walking in Hackney at night.</p>

<p>The former Home Secretary also faced strong criticism over her role in the arrest of Tory MP Damian Green in a leak inquiry.</p>

<p>She also faced embarrassment when it emerged that one in five foreigners cleared to work in security jobs were illegal immigrants.</p>

<p>She lost her Commons seat in 2010 following a row over her expenses involving second homes and porn films watched by her husband,</p>

<p>New challenge: Jacqui will join HRVY, Jason Bell, Ranvir Singh, Clara Amfo, Caroline Quentin, Jamie Laing, Bill Bailey, JJ Chalmers, Max George, Maisie Smith and Nicola Adams</p>

